reviews.title: There's a lot of room for improvement.
reviews.text:
If you then make a reservation with a starter and want to give them a chance to present themselves as an asset, you will unfortunately come home from a cold carnival.
Upon arrival, two staff members are at the door and instead of a greeting you receive a look that means "should you be here"
Then you notice that you enter a fairly atmosphereless place where the other staff can also conjure up a smile with great difficulty.
Anyway, we come to eat so we have to judge that.
What we were already afraid of becomes reality, the waiter regularly makes the mistake of forgetting the drink order, when I order a white wine with the starter, a lean carpaccio, I want it with the starter and not when I have consumed 75% of it.
The carpaccio was very thinly sliced and had to be scraped off the plate, for that price a real travesty, my partner's tomato soup was optimal and turned out to be the only success afterwards.
With the main course, for me the beef and my partner the schnitzel a mini container of warm vegetables consisting of a shredded beetroot with an onion, to be called very lean.
French fries but ordered immediately because this standard tray made people immediately more hungry, the bowl of salad was also very lean and quite tasteless.
A glass of red wine may well contain a nice bottom for the requested price, but the glass was just a little more than wet, moreover had to be asked for this again repeatedly.
The schnitzel was unfortunately the pressed known factory schnitzel and for someone with the reputation of Fresh Specialist we could have expected a little more.
When it turns out afterwards that a glass of white wine has been overcharged we come to the conclusion that this restaurant falls short on many levels and really needs to make a lot of adjustments to become a success on the market in Kerkrade.
If one has pretensions, then live up to them, at the moment one falls short in everything.

reviews.title: Dinner at Bram was disappointing
reviews.text: Service was very friendly and attentive. Chairs are pleasant to sit.  Salads were very disappointing, little dressing, lettuce looked like from a mixed lettuce bag from the supermarket, 2 cherry tomatoes on top, chicken was only moderate and put in slices on salad. Sparrib's taste wasn't bad but it wasn't super either. Salad too simple. French fries not nicely fried. Prices for these products too high. Won't be going back so soon. Competition in the market and much better. Don't recommend it.

articleContent.title: Experience Aboriginal culture in the Northern Territory

seoInfo.metaDescription: The Aboriginal people have inhabited Australia for over 65,000 years, making them the oldest continuous living culture on Earth. Aboriginal culture is deeply intertwined with the land—and in the Northern Territory, it’s very much alive. Whether you visit the Top End or the Red Centre, experiencing Aboriginal culture is key to an enriching trip.

They say two is better than one—and in Ixtapa-Zihuatanejo, that couldn’t be more true. Ixtapa is modern and vibrant, with luxury resorts, breathtaking views, and settings surrounded by lush tropical nature. Zihuatanejo, a Pueblo Mágico, offers cobblestone streets, deep-rooted traditions, and a laid-back coastal vibe. Together, they deliver a travel experience that’s as diverse as it is authentic—earning Ixtapa-Zihuatanejo its place among Mexico’s top beach destinations.

review.title: Dinner bij Bram viel tegen
review.text: Bediening was heel vriendelijk en attent. Stoelen zijn aangenaam om te zitten.  Salades vielen erg tegen, weinig dressing, sla zag uit als uit een gemengde sla zakje uit de supermarkt, 2 cherry tomaatjes erop, kip was maar matig en in schijfjes op salade gelegd. Sparribs smaak was niet slecht maar ook niet super. Salade erbij te simpel. Friet erbij niet lekker gebakken. Prijzen voor deze producten te hoog. Zal er zo gauw niet meer terug gaan. Concurrentie op de markt en heel stuk beter. Beveel het niet aan.
